        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nFew comments/questions from my review so far - \n1)\tBelow API are obsolete references and not supported in VESCollector. The VES documentation should be updated – this should be worked with Alok Gupta.\n${VES_THROTTLE_STATE_EVENT_PATH}         /eventListener/v5/clientThrottlingState\n\n2)\tNoticed you had under resources  - VES-5.28.3-dataformat.jsonVES-5.28.3-dataformat.json (and VES-4.27.2-dataformat.json)  -Don’t see reference of this being used (possibly not looking at right place). \nThere was an bug noticed on VES 5.x spec and newer version released is 5.28.4 (available under dcaegen2/collectors/ves/data-formats/). The data-formats were defined as onboarding artifacts – not something used in run-time.",
